1.title: Humane Society of the United States
1.plot: Giovanna meets with Stephanie Twinning of the Humane Society of the United States, headquartered in Gaithersburg, Maryland to talk about their mission as well as their Pets in the Workplace program. Here you'll see lots of dogs working, working on computers, napping, and not working at all. However, we'd have to agree with Stephanie that their program is definitely a "pawsitive" work place benefit.

2.title: Crumbs and Whiskers
2.plot: Feeling frisky? These kitties are. Join Giovanna as she travels to the nation's capital, Washington DC to visit their first cat cafe. Crumbs and Whiskers is the purrrfect location to have coffee with cats, a day date, or take home your date...errr...we mean take home a kitty.

3.title: Lost Dog and Cat Rescue
3.plot: Giovanna speaks with Pam McAlwee, founder of Lost Dog Cafe and Lost Dog and Cat Rescue Foundation. Learn how the restaurant and the rescue started and how you can adopt one of your very own, limited edition, Lost Dog Rescue Foundation cat or dog.

4.title: Lost Dog Café
4.plot: Giovanna talks with Michael Danner, co-owner of Lost Dog Cafe in Fairfax, Virginia. They talk dogs, hot dogs, dog floats, good dogs, and bad dogs. Well, they're mostly talking about the dog friendly patio and their delicious menu items. As a bonus, you'll be the judge to whether Michael looks like his chihuahua mix Moose, or if Moose looks like his owner Michael.

5.title: Pets in the Workplace
5.plot: Does your dog need a job? Bring them to work. Giovanna talks with Marrisa Landau of the Humane Society of the United States on how to get your company to allow pets in the workplace. Willie was not able to attend. But we're sure it's because he had a lot of work to do from home. What would you do if your office allowed you to bring your dog to work?

imdb.title: emBark! TV
plot: Sharing stories to inspire and illuminate, the emBARK team reveals unique and distinct achievements, innovations and discoveries benefiting our many furry friends.
